      "rationale": "Model form selections justified by literature review and sensitivity analysis: (1) isotropic linear elasticity for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) with bilinear isotropic hardening for post-yield behavior — justified by monotonic loading and well-characterized material data; (2) UHMWPE modeled as hyperelastic (Mooney-Rivlin, 2-parameter) — justified by literature data and confirmed by block compression tests; (3) screw-rod interface modeled as frictional contact (Coulomb, μ=0.2) — justified by tribology literature for titanium-on-titanium. Sensitivity analysis confirms model form uncertainty is secondary to experimental scatter. Gradation 3: formal model form justification with literature support and sensitivity confirmation.",
